==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spinelle
<hw>Spi*nelle"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>spinelle</ets>, or LL.
<ets>spinellus</ets>, perhaps from L. <ets>spina</ets> a thorn, a
prickle, in allusion to its pointed crystals.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral occurring in octahedrons of great hardness and various
colors, as red, green, blue, brown, and black, the red variety being the
gem spinel ruby. It consist essentially of alumina and magnesia, but
commonly contains iron and sometimes also chromium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <xex>spinel group</xex> includes spinel proper, also
magnetite, chromite, franklinite, gahnite, etc., all of which may be
regarded as composed of a sesquioxide and a protoxide in equal
proportions.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spinel</ent>⟦br⟧
